686//
687// Blend State
688//
690
691// Keep BLEND values in sync with earlier DX versions (HW consumes values directly).
692typedef enum D3D12_BLEND
693{
694 D3D12_BLEND_ZERO = 1,
695 D3D12_BLEND_ONE = 2,
696 D3D12_BLEND_SRC_COLOR = 3, // PS output oN.rgb (N is current RT being blended)
697 D3D12_BLEND_INV_SRC_COLOR = 4, // 1.0f - PS output oN.rgb
698 D3D12_BLEND_SRC_ALPHA = 5, // PS output oN.a
699 D3D12_BLEND_INV_SRC_ALPHA = 6, // 1.0f - PS output oN.a
700 D3D12_BLEND_DEST_ALPHA = 7, // RT(N).a (N is current RT being blended)
701 D3D12_BLEND_INV_DEST_ALPHA = 8, // 1.0f - RT(N).a
702 D3D12_BLEND_DEST_COLOR = 9, // RT(N).rgb
703 D3D12_BLEND_INV_DEST_COLOR = 10,// 1.0f - RT(N).rgb
704 D3D12_BLEND_SRC_ALPHA_SAT = 11,// (f,f,f,1), f = min(1 - RT(N).a, oN.a)
705 // 12 reserved (was BOTHSRCALPHA)
706 // 13 reserved (was BOTHSRCALPHA)
707 D3D12_BLEND_BLEND_FACTOR = 14,
708 D3D12_BLEND_INV_BLEND_FACTOR = 15,
709 D3D12_BLEND_SRC1_COLOR = 16, // PS output o1.rgb
710 D3D12_BLEND_INV_SRC1_COLOR = 17, // 1.0f - PS output o1.rgb
711 D3D12_BLEND_SRC1_ALPHA = 18, // PS output o1.a
712 D3D12_BLEND_INV_SRC1_ALPHA = 19, // 1.0f - PS output o1.a
713 D3D12_BLEND_ALPHA_FACTOR = 20,
714 D3D12_BLEND_INV_ALPHA_FACTOR = 21
715} D3D12_BLEND;
716
717// Keep BLENDOP values in sync with earlier DX versions (HW consumes values directly).
718typedef enum D3D12_BLEND_OP
719{
720 D3D12_BLEND_OP_ADD = 1,
721 D3D12_BLEND_OP_SUBTRACT = 2,
722 D3D12_BLEND_OP_REV_SUBTRACT = 3,
723 D3D12_BLEND_OP_MIN = 4, // min semantics are like min shader instruction
724 D3D12_BLEND_OP_MAX = 5, // max semantics are like max shader instruction
725} D3D12_BLEND_OP;

743 D3D12_LOGIC_OP_COPY, // s
744 D3D12_LOGIC_OP_COPY_INVERTED, // ~s
745 D3D12_LOGIC_OP_NOOP, // d
746 D3D12_LOGIC_OP_INVERT, // ~d
747 D3D12_LOGIC_OP_AND, // s & d
748 D3D12_LOGIC_OP_NAND, // ~(s & d)
749 D3D12_LOGIC_OP_OR, // s | d
750 D3D12_LOGIC_OP_NOR, // ~(s | d)
751 D3D12_LOGIC_OP_XOR, // s ^ d
752 D3D12_LOGIC_OP_EQUIV, // ~(s ^ d)
753 D3D12_LOGIC_OP_AND_REVERSE, // s & ~d
754 D3D12_LOGIC_OP_AND_INVERTED, // ~s & d
755 D3D12_LOGIC_OP_OR_REVERSE, // s | ~d
756 D3D12_LOGIC_OP_OR_INVERTED, // ~s | d
757} D3D12_LOGIC_OP;

2240typedef enum D3D12_FILTER
2241{
2242 // Bits used in defining enumeration of valid filters:
2243 // bits [1:0] - mip: 0 == point, 1 == linear, 2,3 unused
2244 // bits [3:2] - mag: 0 == point, 1 == linear, 2,3 unused
2245 // bits [5:4] - min: 0 == point, 1 == linear, 2,3 unused
2246 // bit [6] - aniso
2247 // bits [8:7] - reduction type:
2248 // 0 == standard filtering
2249 // 1 == comparison
2250 // 2 == min
2251 // 3 == max
2252 // bit [31] - mono 1-bit (narrow-purpose filter) [no longer supported in D3D12]
2253
2254 D3D12_FILTER_MIN_MAG_MIP_POINT = 0x00000000,
2255 D3D12_FILTER_MIN_MAG_POINT_MIP_LINEAR = 0x00000001,
2256 D3D12_FILTER_MIN_POINT_MAG_LINEAR_MIP_POINT = 0x00000004,
2257 D3D12_FILTER_MIN_POINT_MAG_MIP_LINEAR = 0x00000005,
2258 D3D12_FILTER_MIN_LINEAR_MAG_MIP_POINT = 0x00000010,
2259 D3D12_FILTER_MIN_LINEAR_MAG_POINT_MIP_LINEAR = 0x00000011,
2260 D3D12_FILTER_MIN_MAG_LINEAR_MIP_POINT = 0x00000014,
2261 D3D12_FILTER_MIN_MAG_MIP_LINEAR = 0x00000015,
2262 D3D12_FILTER_MIN_MAG_ANISOTROPIC_MIP_POINT = 0x00000054,
2263 D3D12_FILTER_ANISOTROPIC = 0x00000055,
2264 D3D12_FILTER_COMPARISON_MIN_MAG_MIP_POINT = 0x00000080,
2265 D3D12_FILTER_COMPARISON_MIN_MAG_POINT_MIP_LINEAR = 0x00000081,
2266 D3D12_FILTER_COMPARISON_MIN_POINT_MAG_LINEAR_MIP_POINT = 0x00000084,
2267 D3D12_FILTER_COMPARISON_MIN_POINT_MAG_MIP_LINEAR = 0x00000085,
2268 D3D12_FILTER_COMPARISON_MIN_LINEAR_MAG_MIP_POINT = 0x00000090,
2269 D3D12_FILTER_COMPARISON_MIN_LINEAR_MAG_POINT_MIP_LINEAR = 0x00000091,
2270 D3D12_FILTER_COMPARISON_MIN_MAG_LINEAR_MIP_POINT = 0x00000094,
2271 D3D12_FILTER_COMPARISON_MIN_MAG_MIP_LINEAR = 0x00000095,
2272 D3D12_FILTER_COMPARISON_MIN_MAG_ANISOTROPIC_MIP_POINT = 0x000000d4,
2273 D3D12_FILTER_COMPARISON_ANISOTROPIC = 0x000000d5,
2274 D3D12_FILTER_MINIMUM_MIN_MAG_MIP_POINT = 0x00000100,
2275 D3D12_FILTER_MINIMUM_MIN_MAG_POINT_MIP_LINEAR = 0x00000101,
2276 D3D12_FILTER_MINIMUM_MIN_POINT_MAG_LINEAR_MIP_POINT = 0x00000104,
2277 D3D12_FILTER_MINIMUM_MIN_POINT_MAG_MIP_LINEAR = 0x00000105,
2278 D3D12_FILTER_MINIMUM_MIN_LINEAR_MAG_MIP_POINT = 0x00000110,
2279 D3D12_FILTER_MINIMUM_MIN_LINEAR_MAG_POINT_MIP_LINEAR = 0x00000111,
2280 D3D12_FILTER_MINIMUM_MIN_MAG_LINEAR_MIP_POINT = 0x00000114,
2281 D3D12_FILTER_MINIMUM_MIN_MAG_MIP_LINEAR = 0x00000115,
2282 D3D12_FILTER_MINIMUM_MIN_MAG_ANISOTROPIC_MIP_POINT = 0x00000154,
2283 D3D12_FILTER_MINIMUM_ANISOTROPIC = 0x00000155,
2284 D3D12_FILTER_MAXIMUM_MIN_MAG_MIP_POINT = 0x00000180,
2285 D3D12_FILTER_MAXIMUM_MIN_MAG_POINT_MIP_LINEAR = 0x00000181,
2286 D3D12_FILTER_MAXIMUM_MIN_POINT_MAG_LINEAR_MIP_POINT = 0x00000184,
2287 D3D12_FILTER_MAXIMUM_MIN_POINT_MAG_MIP_LINEAR = 0x00000185,
2288 D3D12_FILTER_MAXIMUM_MIN_LINEAR_MAG_MIP_POINT = 0x00000190,
2289 D3D12_FILTER_MAXIMUM_MIN_LINEAR_MAG_POINT_MIP_LINEAR = 0x00000191,
2290 D3D12_FILTER_MAXIMUM_MIN_MAG_LINEAR_MIP_POINT = 0x00000194,
2291 D3D12_FILTER_MAXIMUM_MIN_MAG_MIP_LINEAR = 0x00000195,
2292 D3D12_FILTER_MAXIMUM_MIN_MAG_ANISOTROPIC_MIP_POINT = 0x000001d4,
2293 D3D12_FILTER_MAXIMUM_ANISOTROPIC = 0x000001d5
2294} D3D12_FILTER;

2302typedef enum D3D12_FILTER_REDUCTION_TYPE
2303{
2304 D3D12_FILTER_REDUCTION_TYPE_STANDARD = 0,
2305 D3D12_FILTER_REDUCTION_TYPE_COMPARISON = 1,
2306 D3D12_FILTER_REDUCTION_TYPE_MINIMUM = 2,
2307 D3D12_FILTER_REDUCTION_TYPE_MAXIMUM = 3,
2308} D3D12_FILTER_REDUCTION_TYPE;
2309
2310const UINT D3D12_FILTER_REDUCTION_TYPE_MASK = 0x00000003;
2311const UINT D3D12_FILTER_REDUCTION_TYPE_SHIFT = 7;
2312
2313const UINT D3D12_FILTER_TYPE_MASK = 0x00000003;
2314const UINT D3D12_MIN_FILTER_SHIFT = 4;
2315const UINT D3D12_MAG_FILTER_SHIFT = 2;
2316const UINT D3D12_MIP_FILTER_SHIFT = 0;
2317
2318const UINT D3D12_ANISOTROPIC_FILTERING_BIT = 0x00000040;

2320// encode enum entry for most filters except anisotropic filtering
2321cpp_quote( "#define D3D12_ENCODE_BASIC_FILTER( min, mag, mip, reduction ) \\" )
2322cpp_quote( " ( ( D3D12_FILTER ) ( \\" )
2323cpp_quote( " ( ( ( min ) & D3D12_FILTER_TYPE_MASK ) << D3D12_MIN_FILTER_SHIFT ) | \\" )
2324cpp_quote( " ( ( ( mag ) & D3D12_FILTER_TYPE_MASK ) << D3D12_MAG_FILTER_SHIFT ) | \\" )
2325cpp_quote( " ( ( ( mip ) & D3D12_FILTER_TYPE_MASK ) << D3D12_MIP_FILTER_SHIFT ) | \\" )
2326cpp_quote( " ( ( ( reduction ) & D3D12_FILTER_REDUCTION_TYPE_MASK ) << D3D12_FILTER_REDUCTION_TYPE_SHIFT ) ) ) " )
2327
2328// encode enum entry for anisotropic filtering (with or without comparison filtering)
2329cpp_quote( "#define D3D12_ENCODE_ANISOTROPIC_FILTER( reduction ) \\" )
2330cpp_quote( " ( ( D3D12_FILTER ) ( \\" )
2331cpp_quote( " D3D12_ANISOTROPIC_FILTERING_BIT | \\" )
2332cpp_quote( " D3D12_ENCODE_BASIC_FILTER( D3D12_FILTER_TYPE_LINEAR, \\" )
2333cpp_quote( " D3D12_FILTER_TYPE_LINEAR, \\" )
2334cpp_quote( " D3D12_FILTER_TYPE_LINEAR, \\" )
2335cpp_quote( " reduction ) ) ) " )
2336cpp_quote( "#define D3D12_ENCODE_MIN_MAG_ANISOTROPIC_MIP_POINT_FILTER( reduction ) \\" )
2337cpp_quote( " ( ( D3D12_FILTER ) ( \\" )
2338cpp_quote( " D3D12_ANISOTROPIC_FILTERING_BIT | \\" )
2339cpp_quote( " D3D12_ENCODE_BASIC_FILTER( D3D12_FILTER_TYPE_LINEAR, \\" )
2340cpp_quote( " D3D12_FILTER_TYPE_LINEAR, \\" )
2341cpp_quote( " D3D12_FILTER_TYPE_POINT, \\" )
2342cpp_quote( " reduction ) ) ) " )
2343
2344cpp_quote( "#define D3D12_DECODE_MIN_FILTER( D3D12Filter ) \\" )
2345cpp_quote( " ( ( D3D12_FILTER_TYPE ) \\" )
2346cpp_quote( " ( ( ( D3D12Filter ) >> D3D12_MIN_FILTER_SHIFT ) & D3D12_FILTER_TYPE_MASK ) ) " )
2347
2348cpp_quote( "#define D3D12_DECODE_MAG_FILTER( D3D12Filter ) \\" )
2349cpp_quote( " ( ( D3D12_FILTER_TYPE ) \\" )
2350cpp_quote( " ( ( ( D3D12Filter ) >> D3D12_MAG_FILTER_SHIFT ) & D3D12_FILTER_TYPE_MASK ) ) " )
2351
2352cpp_quote( "#define D3D12_DECODE_MIP_FILTER( D3D12Filter ) \\" )
2353cpp_quote( " ( ( D3D12_FILTER_TYPE ) \\" )
2354cpp_quote( " ( ( ( D3D12Filter ) >> D3D12_MIP_FILTER_SHIFT ) & D3D12_FILTER_TYPE_MASK ) ) " )
2355
2356cpp_quote( "#define D3D12_DECODE_FILTER_REDUCTION( D3D12Filter ) \\" )
2357cpp_quote( " ( ( D3D12_FILTER_REDUCTION_TYPE ) \\" )
2358cpp_quote( " ( ( ( D3D12Filter ) >> D3D12_FILTER_REDUCTION_TYPE_SHIFT ) & D3D12_FILTER_REDUCTION_TYPE_MASK ) ) " )
2359
2360cpp_quote( "#define D3D12_DECODE_IS_COMPARISON_FILTER( D3D12Filter ) \\" )
2361cpp_quote( " ( D3D12_DECODE_FILTER_REDUCTION( D3D12Filter ) == D3D12_FILTER_REDUCTION_TYPE_COMPARISON ) " )
2362
2363cpp_quote( "#define D3D12_DECODE_IS_ANISOTROPIC_FILTER( D3D12Filter ) \\" )
2364cpp_quote( " ( ( ( D3D12Filter ) & D3D12_ANISOTROPIC_FILTERING_BIT ) && \\" )
2365cpp_quote( " ( D3D12_FILTER_TYPE_LINEAR == D3D12_DECODE_MIN_FILTER( D3D12Filter ) ) && \\" )
2366cpp_quote( " ( D3D12_FILTER_TYPE_LINEAR == D3D12_DECODE_MAG_FILTER( D3D12Filter ) ) ) " )

6206cpp_quote("// --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------")
6207cpp_quote("// D3D12EnableExperimentalFeatures")
6208cpp_quote("//")
6209cpp_quote("// Pass in a list of feature GUIDs to be enabled together.")
6210cpp_quote("// ")
6211cpp_quote("// If a particular feature requires some configuration information on enablement, it will have")
6212cpp_quote("// a configuration struct that can be passed alongside the GUID.")
6213cpp_quote("// ")
6214cpp_quote("// Some features might use an interface IID as the GUID. For these, once the feature is enabled via")
6215cpp_quote("// D3D12EnableExperimentalFeatures, D3D12GetDebugInterface can then be called with the IID to retrieve the interface")
6216cpp_quote("// for manipulating the feature. This allows for control that might not cleanly be expressed by just ")
6217cpp_quote("// the configuration struct that D3D12EnableExperimentalFeatures provides.")
6218cpp_quote("//")
6219cpp_quote("// If this method is called and a change to existing feature enablement is made, ")
6220cpp_quote("// all current D3D12 devices are set to DEVICE_REMOVED state, since under the covers there is really only one")
6221cpp_quote("// singleton device for a process. Removing the devices when configuration changes prevents")
6222cpp_quote("// mismatched expectations of how a device is supposed to work after it has been created from the app's point of view.")
6223cpp_quote("//")
6224cpp_quote("// The call returns E_NOINTERFACE if an unrecognized feature is passed in or Windows Developer mode is not on.")
6225cpp_quote("// The call returns E_INVALIDARG if the configuration of a feature is incorrect, the set of features passed")
6226cpp_quote("// in are known to be incompatible with each other, or other errors.")
6227cpp_quote("// Returns S_OK otherwise.")
6228cpp_quote("//")
6229cpp_quote("// --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------")
6230cpp_quote("HRESULT WINAPI D3D12EnableExperimentalFeatures(")
6231cpp_quote(" UINT NumFeatures,")
6232cpp_quote(" _In_count_(NumFeatures) const IID* pIIDs,")
6233cpp_quote(" _In_opt_count_(NumFeatures) void* pConfigurationStructs,")
6234cpp_quote(" _In_opt_count_(NumFeatures) UINT* pConfigurationStructSizes);")
6235cpp_quote("")
